SUPPLEMENTARY DETAILS

Technical specifications and implementation details:
- Use Number.isInteger to detect integers with correct semantics for NaN, Infinity and non-number types.
- Use explicit RangeError instances: throw new RangeError('n must be an integer between 1 and 1000000') with concrete limit if applied.
- For array creation, pre-allocate via new Array(n) and populate via for loop using zero-based indices to reduce push overhead when performance matters.
- For generator implementations, perform validation at the start, then use for (let i = 1; i <= n; ++i) { if (i % 15 === 0) yield 'FizzBuzz'; else if (i % 3 === 0) yield 'Fizz'; else if (i % 5 === 0) yield 'Buzz'; else yield String(i); }
- Avoid repeated string conversions by calling String(i) only for the else branch per iteration.
- For combined checks, using i % 15 === 0 is slightly cheaper than checking both i % 3 === 0 && i % 5 === 0 in most JS engines.

